<h3>For readers</h3>

<h4>What's collected?</h4>

<p>
  The only thing we collect is a few <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_cookie">cookies</a>
  and some technical data, such as your browser type, language preference, and the request timestamp.
  Most of that data only exists temporarily, and it's infeasible to access it when the site is running
  or down, whether it's the site admin or a hacker. However, we do collect potentially
  personally-identifying information like your IP, but these are just for system logs and not stored
  in a database.
</p>

<h4>Why is it collected?</h4>

<p>
  Site functionality and for troubleshooting when applicable.
</p>

